(24, 'Western Civ - Old Times', 'Valley', '{\"desc\":\"Made from Mr. Carson\'s material and the textbook\",\"contnt\":{\"Which empire based their power in the cities of Tyre and Sidon, built a mercantile empire, and founded colonies in Africa, Spain, and Sicily?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Phoenician\"]},\"Which empire settled in Canaan, battled the Philistines, and developed ethical monotheism\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hebrew\"]},\"Which empire developed a high-tech military, centralized political government, and built a large library?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Assyrian\"]},\"Which empire conquered judah, made Babylon their preak city, and was overthrown by rebels from Persia?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Chaldean\"]},\"Which empire had Zoroastrianism as their state religion, overthrew the Chaldeans, consolodated control to a central government?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Persian\"]},\"Which empire was made up of many city states, developed the wirst written alphabet, and developed the Epic of Gilgamesh?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sumerian\"]},\"Which empire built the world\'s first standing army, turned the city of Akkad into a center of trade, and expanded influence under Sargon the Great?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Akkadian\"]},\"Which empire was founded in Babylon after the Akkadian collapse and reached its peak under Hammurabi?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Amorite\"]},\"Which empire had history divided into Kingdoms,  Intermediate Periods, had growth facilitated by fertile silt, and whose rulers maintained ma\'at?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Egyptian\"]},\"Which empire was established in Anatolia, warred frequently with the Egyptians, and developed Iron Smelting?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hittite\"]},\"Who expanded the influence of the Akkadian Empire and built the worlds first standing army?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sargon the Great\"]},\"Who created the first written law code?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hammurabi\"]},\"Who was the famous female pharaoh that expanded Egypt\'s trade and built important stuff?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hatshepsut\"]},\"Who was the pharaoh that tried to impose monotheism upon Egypt?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Akhenaten\"]},\"Who was the pharaoh that built up the Egyptian empire by conquering the Medditeranean Coast?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Rhamses II\"]},\"Who led the Hebrews out of Egypt?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Moses\"]},\"Who set up the united kingdom of Isreal?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Moses\"]},\"What did Isreal experience under David and Solomon?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Golden Age\"]},\"Who was the ruler of Isreal known for their military conquest?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"David\"]},\"Whose son promoted trade and built an important temple for Isreal?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Solomon\"]},\"Who was the god that the Hebrew\'s worshiped?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Yaweh\"]},\"What did Tiglath-Pileser II and Sargon II do for Assyria?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Conquered\"]},\"Under who did the Chaldean empire peak? (absolute chad)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nebuchadnezzar II\"]},\"Who is the god of Zoroastrianism?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Ahura Mazda\"]},\"Who caused the Persian empire to adopt Zoroastrianism?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Darius I\"]},\"What was the branch of monotheism that the Hebrews created?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Ethical Monotheism\"]},\"What was the pact between God and the Hebrews?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Covenant\"]},\"What was the religious text developed by the Judah\'s citizens when they were exiled to Babylon?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Torah\"]},\"What was the river that stimulated the growth of the Egyptians?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nile\"]},\"What was the concept of harmony and justice that permeates the universe?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"ma\'at\"]},\"What was the first written language developed under the Sumerians?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cuneiform\"]},\"What were the stepped pyramids that the Sumerians developed?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Ziggurat\"]},\"What was the Sumerian story which detailed the search for Immortality?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Epic of Gilgamesh\"]},\"What was the battle that led to a peace treaty between the Hittites and Egyptians?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Battle of Kadesh\"]},\"What was the Egyptian work that detailed a guide about how to be a good dead person?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Book of the Dead\"]},\"What was the name of a Persian local government official?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Satrap\"]}}}', '[5,1,13,7,10,2,3]', 1),
(26, 'Spanish II Unit 0 - All vocab', 'bitfeller', '{\"desc\":\"Credit to Mrs. Mozingo for originally making this vocab on Quizlet. --- All vocab for Lesson 0 of Spanish 2.\",\"contnt\":{\"What&amp;#039;s the weather like?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"¿Qué tiempo hace?\"]},\"The weather is good/bad\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hace buen/mal tiempo\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s hot\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hace calor\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s cold\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hace frío\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s raining\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Está lloviendo\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s snowing\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Está nevando\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s cloudy\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Está nublado\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s cool\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hace fresco\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s sunny\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hace sol\"]},\"It&amp;#039;s windy\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hace viento\"]},\"to have lunch\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"almorzar (o:ue)\"]},\"to close\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"cerrar (e:ie)\"]},\"to begin, to start\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"comenzar (e:ie)\"]},\"to count; to tell\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"contar (o:ue)\"]},\"to say, to tell (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"decir (e:i)\"]},\"to sleep\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"dormir (o:ue)\"]},\"to start, to begin\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"empezar (e:ie)\"]},\"to find\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"encontrar (o:ue)\"]},\"to understand\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"comprender\"]},\"to play\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"jugar (u:ue)\"]},\"to show\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"mostrar (o:ue)\"]},\"to ask for\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"pedir (e:i)\"]},\"to think\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"pensar (e:ie)\"]},\"to lose\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"perder (e:ie)\"]},\"to be able, can\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"poder (o:ue)\"]},\"to prefer\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"preferir (e:ie)\"]},\"to want; to love\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"querer (e:ie)\"]},\"to remember\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"recordar (o:ue)\"]},\"to repeat\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"repetir (e:i)\"]},\"to return\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"regresar\"]},\"to get, obtain (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"conseguir (e:i)\"]},\"to do, to make (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"hacer\"]},\"to hear (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"oír\"]},\"to put, place (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"poner\"]},\"to leave (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"salir\"]},\"to follow, to continue (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"seguir (e:i)\"]},\"to suppose that (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"suponer (que)\"]},\"to have (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"tener\"]},\"to bring (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"traer\"]},\"to come (yo-go)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"venir\"]},\"Yo ___ inteligente.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"soy\"]},\"Rafael y yo___ muy trabajadores. (hardworking)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"somos\"]},\"Susana y Mary no ________amigas.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"son\"]},\"Mi mamá ____ cansada (tired).\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"está\"]},\"Tú ___ de Cuba, ¿no?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"eres\"]},\"Tú ____ triste, Juanito.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"estás\"]},\"Yo ___ en la casa.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"estoy\"]},\"Nosotros ___ contentos hoy.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"estamos\"]}}}', '[1,3,2,19]', 1),
(27, 'Western Civ. Unit 1', 'EnlightenedMycorrhizae703', '{\"desc\":\"These are the terms, civilizations, time periods and important names from the Paleolithic Era to ancient Israel and Persia.\",\"contnt\":{\"the king who united Israel and ruled a Golden Age\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"David\"]},\"the king of Israel who succeeded David, and after his rule, Israel split\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Solomon\"]},\"the Babylonian king who wrote a famous code of laws\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hammurabi\"]},\"the Hebrew prophet who was considered the first monotheist\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Abraham\"]},\"the Egyptian pharaoh who faced military difficulties with the Hittites, but signed a peace treaty with them\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Ramses II\"]},\"the Hebrew prophet who led the Exodus out of Egypt\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Moses\"]},\"the Egyptian pharaoh who unsuccessfully attempted to convert his people into monotheists\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Akhenaten\"]},\"the Egyptian god who judged the dead and was said to have been cut into countless pieces, but was resurrected\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Osiris\"]},\"the Chaldean ruler who conquered Judah and Jerusalem\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nebuchadnezzar II\"]},\"the Persian ruler who built his empire and was known for treating his conquered subjects with tolerance\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cyrus the Great\"]},\"the Addadian king who conquered Sumer\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sargon the Great\"]},\"a civilization that conquered northern Israel when the kingdom split\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Assyria\"]},\"a civilization that tolerated its diverse subjects and divided its empire into provinces ruled by satraps; Zoroastrianism\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Persia\"]},\"a civilization in Mesopotamia that conquered Sumer and had the first standing army\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Akkad\"]},\"a civilization in Mesopotamia that is known for Hammurabi&amp;#039;s Code\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Babylon\"]},\"a civilization that thrived with trade across the Mediterranean; known for purple textiles, shipbuilding, and the first alphabet\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Phonecia\"]},\"a civilization that began iron smelting in Anatolia and was militaristic\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hittite\"]},\"a civilization that conquered Judah and became rich; &amp;quot;Neo-Babylon&amp;quot;\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Chaldea\"]},\"a group of people who founded Israel and developed Judaism\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hebrews\"]},\"a civilization built around the Nile that was known for pharaohs, pyramids, hieroglyphics, and mummification\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Egypt\"]},\"the oldest civilization known; in Mesopotamia; characterized by cuneiform, wheels, polytheism, and the Epic of Gilgamesh\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sumer\"]},\"about 1100 BCE to 550 BCE, when iron was the best material with which to build tools\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Iron Age\"]},\"about 250,000 BCE to 9000 BCE, when stone tools were used and foraging was the only way to obtain food\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Paleolithic Era\"]},\"about 3000-2500 BCE to 1200-300 BCE, when bronze was a widely used but expensive material\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Bronze Age\"]},\"about 9000 BCE to 2500 BCE, when agriculture existed, but natural materials were used for tools\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Neolithic Era\"]},\"an Egyptian monarch who was considered divine\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"pharaoh\"]},\"the belief in one god\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"monotheism\"]},\"the first writing system; used a wedge (stylus) to press marks into wet clay\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"cuneiform\"]},\"two rivers in the Fertile Crescent\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Tigris and Euphrates\"]},\"the belief in many gods\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"polytheism\"]},\"the land from the eastern Mediterranean to the Tigris and Euphrates Rivers\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Fertile Crescent\"]},\"the land between the Tigris and Euphrates Rivers where the first civilizations arose\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Mesopotamia\"]},\"a river that runs through the eastern Sahara and is the heart of Egypt\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nile\"]},\"the domestication and herding of animals\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"pastoralism\"]},\"the holy text of Judaism\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Torah\"]},\"a code of laws that was very strict and very famous\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hammurabi&amp;#039;s Code\"]},\"the agreement between the Hebrews and Yahweh stating that they would worship only Yahweh, and in return, they would be protected\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Covenant\"]},\"a term that has changed meaning many times, but now refers to Europe (and the nations that align with it)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Western Civilization\"]},\"the name that the Hebrews called God\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Yahweh\"]},\"a Persian governor who deals with provincial affairs\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"satrap\"]},\"the first epic poem telling of a king&amp;#039;s quest for immortality; contains the first flood myth\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Epic of Gilgamesh\"]},\"a grand, triangular tomb with a square base constructed for pharaohs\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"pyramid\"]},\"the religion that believes that humans must align themselves with the benevolent Ahura Mazda\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Zoroastrianism\"]}}}', '[10,1,3,14,2,22]', 1),
(28, 'English Vocabulary 2 (list 3+$', 'JBR33ZY', '{\"desc\":\"banana\",\"contnt\":{\"verb -- to act as a person chosen to settle difference between two parties\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"arbitrate\"]},\"adverb -- in parts; a part from one another in position\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"asunder\"]},\"noun -- an inherent characteristic; an object closely associated with or belonging to a person or office --verb--to explain by indicating a cause\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"attribute\"]},\"verb -- to make greater or more numerous\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"augment\"]},\"noun -- greed\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"avarice\"]},\"noun--a bower of branches or vines or of a lattice work covered with climbing vines or shrubs\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"arbor\"]},\"adjective -- practicing strict self-denial as a measure of personal and esp. spiritual discipline; austereinmanner, appearance, orattitude\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"ascetic\"]},\"noun -- an examination and determination as to characteristics; analysis\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"assay\"]},\"verb transitive -- to turn away or aside in avoidance\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"avert\"]},\"noun -- the blue color of the clear sky\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"azure\"]},\"noun -- an aromatic preparation (as in a healing ointment); a soothing restorative\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"balm\"]},\"noun -- one that confers a benefit: one who makes a gift or bequest\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"benefactor\"]},\"verb transitive -- to surround with armed forces; to press with requests; to cause worry or distress to\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"besiege\"]},\"noun -- to speak of or address irreverence; torevile, abuse: speak (----)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"blasphemy\"]},\"adjective -- useless\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"bootless\"]},\"verb transitive -- to shake or wave menacingly\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"brandish\"]},\"noun -- muscular strength; in Britain, the flesh of a boar\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"brawn\"]},\"noun --&amp;nbsp;width; a wide expanse; scope\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"breadth\"]},\"noun --&amp;nbsp;shortness of duration; expression in few words\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"brevity\"]},\"noun\\/verb --&amp;nbsp;a projecting structure giving support to a wall or building; something that supports or strengthens\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"buttress\"]}}}', '[1,3,14,2]', 1);
INSERT INTO `decks` (`id`, `name`, `owner`, `data`, `viewdata`, `public`) VALUES
(29, 'Western Civ - Classics', 'Valley', '{\"desc\":\"A collection of ancient Greek and Roman historical figures, concepts, and events.\",\"contnt\":{\"Who was the ancient Greek poet known for writing Theogony and Works and Days?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hesiod\"]},\"Who was the tyrant that seized power and established peace in Athens?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Pisistratus\"]},\"What were the name of the heavily armed foot soldiers of Ancient Greece that played an essential role in phalanxes?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hoplites\"]},\"Who was the king of Macedon who united most of Greece, preparing the kingdom for his sons rule?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Philip II of Macedon\",\"Philip II\"]},\"Who is often called the Father of History and authored the History of the Persian wars?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Herodotus\"]},\"Who was the ancient Greek historian who wrote about the Peloponnesian War?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Thucydides\"]},\"Who is known as the Father of Geometry and wrote the Elements, an influential geometry textbook?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Euclid\"]},\"Who was the ancient Greek philosopher sentenced to death for impiety and corrupting youth, and created a novel method of discussion?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Socrates\"]},\"Who was the ancient Greek mathematician and Astronomer that measured the circumference of the Earth?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Eratosthenes\"]},\"Which ancient Greek mathematician made significant contributions to geometry and mechanics, and discovered the principle of buoyancy?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Archimedes\"]},\"What was the earliest civilization on the Balkan Peninsula, that developed linear-a?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Minoan\"]},\"Who was the Athenian statesman credited with laying the foundations for democracy in Athens?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Solon\"]},\"What term describes a form of government where power is in the hands of a few?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Oligarchy\"]},\"What was the public open space in ancient Greek cities used for trade and civic duties?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Agora\"]},\"What term refers to the fortified hilltop found in many ancient Greek cities?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Acropolis\"]},\"Who was the ancient Greek playwright known for his tragedies, including Oedipus Rex?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sophocles\"]},\"Which playwright is considered the father of New Comedy in Ancient Greece?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Menander\"]},\"Who was the philosopher, student of Socrates, that founded the Academy in Athens authored The Republic, and developed The Theory of Forms?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Plato\"]},\"Which ancient Greek astronomer proposed that the Earth orbits the sun, a heliocentric view?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Aristarchus\"]},\"What philosophy teaches that pleasure is the highest good, but advocates moderation?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Epicureanism\"]},\"What was the warlike Greek Civilization during the Bronze Age that supported Artisans, and had fortified towns like Argos.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Mycenaean\"]},\"Which reformer is credited with establishing the foundations of Athenian democracy?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cleisthenes\"]},\"What term refers to the rule by one who seized power unconstitutionally in ancient Greece?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Tyranny\"]},\"What term refers to the urban center of ancient Greek city-states?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Asty\"]},\"What term refers to the rural territory surrounding an ancient Greek city-state?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Chora\"]},\"Who was the great tragedian that wrote the Oresteia, a trilogy about a royal family falling from grace?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Aeschylus\"]},\"Who was the prominent and influential statesman of Athens during its Golden Age?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Pericles\"]},\"Which philosopher, a student of Plato, created the Lyceum, and tutored Alexander the Great?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Aristotle\"]},\"Who is often regarded as the Father of Medicine, he also notably performed ethical medical treatments?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hippocrates\"]},\"Which philosophy advocates rationality and self-control as the means to achieve inner peace?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Stoicism\"]},\"Who was the ancient Greek poet known for composing the epic poems Iliad and Odyssey?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Homer\"]},\"Which Athenian lawmaker was known for his harsh legal code in the 7th century BCE? (He has an English word named after him)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Draco\"]},\"What form of government is characterized by rule by the people, often through elected representatives?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Democracy\"]},\"What was the term for the state-owned serfs in ancient Sparta?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Helot\"]},\"What was the popular assembly of citizens that held the greatest power in Athenian government called?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Ecclesia\"]},\"Which ancient Greek tragedian wrote plays such as Medea and The Bacchae?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Euripides\"]},\"Which ancient Greek playwright was known for his comedies, including The Clouds and Lysistrata?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Aristophanes\"]},\"What were the professional teachers and philosophers in Ancient Greece who questioned traditional beliefs to gain greater understanding called?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sophists\"]},\"What term refers to the early Greek philosophers who preceded Socrates and focused on natural phenomena?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Pre-Socratics\"]},\"Who was the Roman poet famous for writing the Metamorphoses and the Art of Love?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Ovid\"]},\"Which Roman poet is known for his lyric poetry, including Odes and Satires?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Horace\"]},\"Who was the Roman general who defeated Hannibal in the Second Punic War, and pacified Spain for Rome?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Scipio Africanus\"]},\"Who was the early Christian missionary and apostle who spread Christianity across the Roman Empire?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Paul\"]},\"Who was the legendary founder and first king of Rome?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Romulus\"]},\"Which Roman general who commanded troops under Sulla joined the First Triumvirate?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Pompey\"]},\"Who was the wealthy Roman politician and member of the First Triumvirate?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Crassus\"]},\"Which Roman emperor is infamous for his tyrannical rule, said to have burned Rome, and murdered his mom?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nero\"]},\"What was the elite unit of the Roman army that served as the bodyguards of the emperor\\u00a0 and played an important political role in Rome?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Praetorian Guard\"]},\"Who was the Roman orator, philosopher, and politician that wrote On Duties, and On Old Age?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cicero\"]},\"Which Roman emperor made Christianity the official state religion of the Roman Empire?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Theodosius I\"]},\"Who was the Carthaginian general famous for crossing the Alps with war elephants during the Second Punic War?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hannibal Barca\",\"Hannibal\"]},\"Who is the central figure of Christianity, believed to be the son of God by Christians?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Jesus of Nazareth\",\"Jesus\"]},\"What term refers to the wealthy, aristocratic class of ancient Rome?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Patricians\"]},\"Who was the Roman general who became dictator for life before being assassinated in 44 BCE, crossed the Rubicon, and conquered Gaul?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Julius Caesar\",\"Caesar\"]},\"Who was the Roman general and lover of Cleopatra, who fought against Octavian?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Mark Antony\"]},\"Which Roman emperor is known for his philosophical writings, especially the Meditations, and was a stoic?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Marcus Aurelius\"]},\"What were the large military units of the Roman army called?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Legions\"]},\"Who was the Roman historian known for his extensive history of Rome, Ab Urbe Condita, which he was paid by Augustus to write?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Livy\"]},\"Which Roman emperor legalized Christianity with the Edict of Milan in 313 CE?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Constantine\"]},\"What civilization heavily influenced the early Romans before they gained independence?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Etruscans\"]},\"Who was the first Roman emperor who established the Pax Romana?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Octavian\"]},\"What term refers to the commoner class in ancient Rome?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Plebeians\"]},\"What was the long struggle between plebeians and patricians for political equality in ancient Rome?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Struggle of the Orders\"]},\"Which Roman emperor expanded the empire to its greatest extent, led Rome to victory against the Parthians, and built a new Roman Forum?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Trajan\"]},\"Who was the Roman poet who wrote the epic poem Aeneid?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Virgil\"]},\"Which Roman reformer was killed for attempting land reforms for the poor?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Tiberius Gracchus\",\"Gaius Gracchus\"]},\"Which Roman philosopher and playwright was a tutor to Nero, and believed in Stoicism?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Seneca\"]},\"Who was the Roman historian known for his works Germania and Annals?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Tacitus\"]},\"What term describes the system of mutual obligations between powerful Roman political elites and people who provide votes in exchange for politcal sway?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Patron Client System\",\"Patron-Client System\",\"Patron Clien\"]},\"What was the highest elected political office in the Roman Republic, held by two individuals?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Consul\"]},\"What was the elected official in ancient Rome who represented the interests of the plebeians?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Tribune\",\"Tribune of the Plebs\",\"Tribune of the Plebeians\"]},\"What was the supreme governing body of ancient Rome, initially composed of aristocrats?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Senate\"]},\"Which Roman emperor is known for building a wall across Britain to keep out invaders, and being a patron of the arts?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hadrian\"]},\"Who was the Roman general and politician who reformed the army and was elected consul seven times?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Marius\"]},\"What was the Roman electoral body that could pass laws, and appoint Consuls, but relied on the Senate?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Centuriate\"]},\"Who were the people living in Sparta, who were free but only had partial citizenship?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Perioikoi\"]},\"Who set up a military dictatorship in Sparta?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Lycurgus\"]},\"Who was the Greek Philosopher that believed water is the basic element of the universe?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Thales\"]},\"What were the close-knit religious groups, that worshiped a certain god, and preached that hidden knowledge would bring them salvation?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Mystery Cults\"]},\"What was the term for the male head of the household in the Imperial Roman Empire?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Pater Patriae\"]},\"Who were the Five Good Emperors (in chronological order because I do no want to add all the variations)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nerva, Trajan, Hadrian, Antoninus Pious, Marcus Aurelius\",\"Nerva Trajan Hadrian AntoninusPious Marcus Aurelius\"]},\"Which emperors were part of the Flavian Dynasty\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Titus, Domitian\",\"Titus Domitian\"]},\"What was the term for worship of the emperor and the Roman state?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Roma et Augustus\"]}}}', '[2,10,14,3,1]', 1),
(32, 'English Vocabulary 3', 'JBR33ZY', '{\"desc\":\"Contains lists 5 and 6\",\"contnt\":{\"N = a procession of riders and carriages: a procession of vehicles or ships: a dramatic sequence of procession\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cavalcade\"]},\"VT = to subject to severe criticism\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Castigate\"]},\"N = a state of being or feeling certain; unfailingness of act or event\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Certitude\"]},\"VT = to inflict punishment on; to censure severely\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Castise\"]},\"V - to speak out in angry or displeased rebuke; to voice disapproval to\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Chide\"]},\"N =  an artificial reservoir for storing liquid, esp. water; a large, usually silver vessel used at the dining table\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cistern\"]},\"N = a fortress that commands a city; stronghold\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Citadel\"]},\"N = an area within a convent or monastery to which the religious are normally restricted; a monastic establishment or life; VT = to seclude from the world as if in a cloister\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cloister\"]},\"ADJ = having special or certain knowledge, esp. from a firsthand source\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cognizant\"]},\"ADJ = accompanying as a subordinate or secondary figure; belonging to the same ancestral stock but not in the direct line of descent; parallel\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Collateral\"]},\"Adj = capable of producing a rapid chemical reaction that results in flame 2) easily excited \":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Combustible\"]},\"V = to tend or move toward one point; to come together\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Converge\"]},\"ADJ = yielding something abundantly\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Copious\"]},\"N = a flirtatious act\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Coquetry\"]},\"ADJ = relating to a physical body: not spiritual or intangible\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Corporeal\"]},\"VT = to include; to be made up of; to make up\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Comprise\"]},\"V = to become pregnant: originate; to take into one\\u2019s mind; to understand\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Conceive\"]},\"N = an act contending (striving in contest); a point advanced or maintained in an argument or debate\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Contention\"]},\"V = devise, form or create in an ingenious manner; to bring about by strategy\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Contrive\"]},\"V = to behave; N = comportment \":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Comport\"]}}}', '[1,14,2,5]', 1),
(33, 'Chem 10 Ions', 'SeanO', '{\"desc\":\"\",\"contnt\":{\"\\u00a0NH4+\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Ammonium\"]},\"C2H3O2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Acetate\"]},\"BrO3-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Bromate\"]},\"ClO3-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Chlorate\"]},\"ClO2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"chlorite\"]},\"CN-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cyanide\"]},\"HCO3-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hydrogen carbonate\"]},\"HSO4-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hydrogen sulfate\"]},\"OH-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hydroxide\"]},\"IO-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hypoiodite\"]},\"IO3-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Iodate\"]},\"NO3-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nitrate\"]},\"NO2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nitrite\"]},\"ClO4-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Perchlorate\"]},\"MnO4-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Permanganate\"]},\"CO3^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Carbonate\"]},\"CrO4^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Chromate\"]},\"Cr2O7^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Dichromate\"]},\"C2O4^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Oxalate\"]},\"O2^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Peroxide\"]},\"SO4^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sulfate\"]},\"SO3^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Sulfite\"]},\"S2O3^2-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Thiosulfate\"]},\"PO4^3-\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Phosphate\"]}}}', '[14,2,22]', 1),
(34, 'English Vocabulary 7+8', 'JBR33ZY', '{\"desc\":\"\",\"contnt\":{\"N = facial expression; bearing or demeanor\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Countenance\"]},\"ADJ\\/ADV = elegant; in a (-) manner\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Courtly\"]},\"V = to shrink away or crouch, quivering from something that menaces, domineers, or dismays\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Cower\"]},\"N = a sharp, detached fragment of rock\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Crag\"]},\"N\\/ADJ = something delicious to taste; tasting good; of a kind of appeal to a fastidious taste esp. because of fragile beauty or diminutive charm\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Dainty\"]},\"ADJ = fearless; unsubdued\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Dauntless\"]},\"V = to trace the course of; to infer from a general principle\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Deduce\"]},\"ADJ = marked by facility and skill\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Deft\"]},\"N = to overflow or swamp; an overflowing of the land by water; an overwhelming amount or number\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Deluge\"]},\"ADJ = reserved; modest\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Demure\"]},\"VT = to feel or express grief for; to consider unfortunate or deserving of deprecation\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Deplore\"]},\"N = the manner in which one conducts oneself\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Deportment\"]},\"V = to take or receive from a specified source; infer or deduce\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Derive\"]},\"V = to turn aside from the norm; characterized by departure from the norm\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Deviate\"]},\"ADJ = indicating small size\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Diminutive\"]},\"ADJ = exciting horror; warning of disaster; desperately urgent\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Dire\"]},\" V = to detect with the eyes; to come to know or recognize mentally; to see or understand the difference\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Discern\"]},\"ADJ = showing discernment or good judgement; unpretentious\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Discreet\"]},\"ADJ = ill-humored\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Disgruntled\"]},\"ADJ = dreadful; showing or causing gloom or depression\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Dismal\"]},\"A style of poetry that expresses sorrow and mourning of past, better times\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Elegiac\"]},\"The practice of assessing a person&#039;s character or personality from their outer appearance\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Physiognomy\"]},\"Rough dramatizations of biblical stories preformed on large wagons or on platforms in marketplaces or innyards\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Miracle Play\"]},\"Elaborate and sophisticated dramatic allegories in which characters representing various virtues and vices confronted one another\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Morality Plays\"]},\"Two consecutive and rhyming lines of verse written in iambic pentameter usually found in a heroic story\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Heroic Couplet\"]},\"A storytelling device in which one story provides the organization of and structure for another tale\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Frame Story\"]},\"A kind of writing that holds up ridicule or contempt for the weaknesses and wrong-doings of individuals, group, institutions, or humanity in general\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Satire\"]}}}', '[14,1,2]', 1),
(35, 'Brit Lit - S1 Midterm', 'Valley', '{\"desc\":\"Made from Mrs. Ford&#039;s gracious review of the test\",\"contnt\":{\"What was an Old English poet or bard that told stories?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Scop\"]},\"What are the figurative compound expression used in Old English poetry\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Kenning\"]},\"Where does the story of Beowulf take place?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"German Countries\"]},\"Which groups brought Germanic Tribes to England\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Angles, Saxons, Jutes\"]},\"What was Elegaic tradition\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"mourning\",\"mourning of the past\"]},\"When did the Normans invade England?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"1066\"]},\"What did William of Normandy bring to England?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"French\"]},\"What is the practice of judging character by appearance?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"physiognomy\"]},\"What is the prioress&#039;s most inappropriate offense?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"gold brooch\"]},\"What signals that the Wife of Bath is scandalous?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"gap in her teeth\",\"red pantyhose\"]},\"Which character in the Canterbury Tales abuses his job by bribing people with church money?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Summoner\",\"The Summoner\"]},\"At what time was the Canterbury Tales set?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"April\",\"Spring\"]},\"What is a brief story used to illustrate a moral truth?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"exemplum\"]},\"What is a general truth or established principle?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"maxim\"]},\"What is the maxim of the Pardoner&#039;s tale?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Greed is the root of all evil\"]},\"Which English King united England, promoted education, and patroned the Anglo-Saxon Chronicles?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Alfred the Great\"]},\"Why did Beowulf&#039;s subjects choose to bury the dragon&#039;s treasure at the end of the story?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"To honor him\",\"honor\"]},\"Who was the greatest writer in Middle English?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Chaucer\"]}}}', '[2,14,8,19,1]', 1),
(40, 'Western Civ - Medieval', 'Valley', '{\"desc\":\"Descriptions and significance of medieval terms.\",\"contnt\":{\"Who was the pope who set standards for papal responsibilities and missions, and protected Rome&#039;s food supply?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Gregory I\"]},\"Who expanded French territories and centralized royal power in France?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Philip II Augustus\"]},\"What term refers to sacred objects linked to saints, believed to offer divine connection?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Relic\",\"Relics\"]},\"What was the term for land on a manor retained by the lord and worked by peasants?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Demesne\"]},\"What were church officials interacting with the laity, administering sacraments without monastic vows?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Secular Clergy\"]},\"Who were clerics living under monastic rules in isolated communities dedicated to prayer and study?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Regular Clergy\"]},\"What was the eastern continuation of the Roman Empire known for its Orthodox Christianity?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Byzantine Empire\",\"Byzantine\"]},\"What legal code, commissioned by Justinian, influenced European law by codifying Roman principles?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Code of Justinian\"]},\"What was the period of cultural revival in France under Charlemagne, under which monks and secular clergy were educated in Latin?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Carolingian Renaissance\"]},\"What cultural period in northern England saw the creation of works like the Lindisfarne Gospels and an extensive library?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Northumbrian Renaissance\",\"Northumbrian\"]},\"Who was a Dominican theologian and scholastic, known for merging faith with Aristotelian philosophy?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Thomas Aquinas\"]},\"What term refers to religious wars initiated by Christian states to reclaim the Holy Land?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Crusades\"]},\"What was the period of food shortages and starvation in early 14th-century Europe, caused by a little ice age and torrential rainstorms?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Great Famine\"]},\"What term describes the primary agrarian labor force, working land under lordly control?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Peasantry\",\"Serfs\",\"Peasant\"]},\"What was a grant by the Church reducing time spent in Purgatory, often obtained through donations?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Indulgence\"]},\"Who was the Muslim leader known for reclaiming Jerusalem from the Crusaders in 1187?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Saladin\"]},\"Who translated the Bible into Latin, creating the Vulgate and promoting classical studies?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"St. Jerome\",\"Jerome\"]},\"What is the term for land granted by a lord to a vassal in return for loyalty and service?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Fief\"]},\"Who were officials overseeing church districts called dioceses, with both spiritual and administrative power?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Bishop\"]},\"What is the office of the Pope, claiming supremacy over all Christians?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Papacy\"]},\"What religious life involves individuals withdrawing from society for ascetic living and prayer?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Monasticism\"]},\"What were associations controlling craft and trade standards in medieval towns, often made by traveling merchants and artisans?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Guilds\",\"Rowen Trading\"]},\"What was the early Frankish dynasty founded by Clovis I who who converted the Franks to Roman Catholic Christianity? \":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Merovingian Dynasty\",\"Merovingian\"]},\"Which Frankish dynasty reached its height under Charlemagne, known for cultural and military achievements, and was formed using marriage alliances by Pippin I?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Carolingian Dynasty\",\"Carolingian\"]},\"Who was the Frankish king and Holy Roman Emperor who united much of Western Europe?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Charlemagne\"]},\"What intellectual movement merged Christian doctrine with classical philosophy in medieval universities?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Scholasticism\"]},\"What architectural style in medieval Europe is known for its flying buttresses, stone ribbed roofs connected by plaster, and stained glass?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Gothic Architecture\",\"Gothic\"]},\"What term describes the land-owning and military elite in medieval European society?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Nobility\",\"Nobles\"]},\"What is the transitional afterlife stage where souls are purified before entering heaven?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Purgatory\"]},\"Who was the Norman ruler who conquered England in 1066, centralizing power under a feudal system?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"William I \",\"William The Conqueror\",\"William\",\"Will\"]},\"What social system involved lords granting land to vassals in exchange for loyalty and service?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Feudalism\"]},\"What economic system structured medieval estates, with peasants working land for their lords?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Manorialism\"]},\"What is the term for a church district overseen by a bishop, organizing Christian communities?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Diocese\"]},\"What set of guidelines created by a 6th-century saint regulated monastic life?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Rule of St. Benedict\",\"St. Benedict\"]},\"Who was the theologian from North Africa influential in Christian doctrine, especially on grace and human will through works such as The City of God?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Augustine of Hippo\"]},\"What was the Muslim kingdom in the Iberian Peninsula, known for its cultural and scientific exchange with Europe?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"al-Andalus\"]},\"Who was the Prophet and founder of Islam, central to the religion\\u2019s teachings in the Quran?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Muhammad\"]},\"What are the core practices of Islam, including faith, prayer, almsgiving, fasting, and pilgrimage?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Five Pillars of Islam\",\"Five Pillars\",\"5 Pillars\"]},\"Who were Norse seafarers known for their raids and trades, affecting Europe in the medieval period?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Vikings\"]},\"What were centers of higher learning in medieval Europe that evolved from cathedral and monastery schools?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Universities\"]},\"What was the pandemic in the 14th century that caused mass mortality and major social upheaval?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Black Death\"]},\"What was the prolonged conflict between England and France, resulting in great nationalism, development of parliament, and French land gains?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hundred Years War\",\"100 Years War\"]},\"Who were members of the clergy, the religious leaders and caretakers of spiritual and church matters?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Clergy\"]},\"What is a coalition of tribes called?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Confederacy\"]},\"What were war bands of tribes called?\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Comitatus\"]}}}', '[2,14,8,1]', 1),
(41, 'English vocab 9+10', 'bitfeller', '{\"desc\":\"\",\"contnt\":{\"temperamental make-up\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"disposition (N)\"]},\"bad humor or temper\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"distemper (N)\"]},\"to extract the essence of\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"distill (V)\"]},\"easily taughtl; easily lead or managed\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"docile (adj)\"]},\"something held as an established opinion; a doctrine or body of doctrines concerning faith or morals as proclaimed by a church\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"dogma (N)\"]},\"mental suffering or anguish\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"dolor (N)\"]},\"part of or interest in the real estate of a deceased husband given by law to his widow during her life; V = to supply with a dower\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"dower (N)\"]},\"of or relating to the church\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"ecclesiastical (adj)\"]},\"producing or able to produce the desired effect\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"effectual (adj)\"]},\"to throw into disorder or confusion; to involve in a conflict\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"embroil (V)\"]},\"position or prominence or superiority\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"eminence (N)\"]},\"to weigh down or burden; to hinder\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"encumber (V)\"]},\"one with sensitive and discriminating tastes\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"epicure (N)\"]},\"to avoid committing oneself to what one says\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"equivocate (V)\"]},\"designed for or understood by the specially initiated group alone; of or relating to knowledge that is restricted to a small group\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"esotoric (adj)\"]},\"of or relating to the regions beyond earth; lacking material substance; marked by unusual refinement of delicacy\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"ethereal (adj)\"]},\"suitable for achieving a particular end;  characterized by concern for what is opportune\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"expedient (adj)\"]},\"to obtain from a person by force or undue illegal power\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"extort (V)\"]},\"of or relating to a self-seeking and contradictory group or party within a government\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"factious (adj)\"]},\"ability or power as either an innate or acquired ability to act\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"faculty (N)\"]},\"Characterized with lack of influence of fate; a psychological or moral flaw in the main character; subplots; differing settings; spectacle (sometimes) onstage\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Shakespearean Tragedy\"]},\"Characteristics of this kind of person: exceptional\\/important; high rank; downfall makes a big impact on those around them; they cause their own downfalls through their actions\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Shakespearean tragic hero\"]},\"Dramatic convention where a character turns aside to speak to a few words directly to the audience\\/another character.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"aside\"]},\"Dramatic convention where character makes big speech alone on stage; often honest\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"soliloquy\"]},\"A long speech in a play delivered by a single person; part of a conversation between one or two other people;\\u00a0\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"monologue\"]},\"Event\\/detail chronologically out of proper time in history\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"anachronism\"]},\"Prevailing mood\\/feeling of literary work\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Atmosphere\"]},\"Attitude a writer takes toward their subject, character, or audience\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"tone\"]},\"Personality\\/traits of a character (don&#039;t overthink this)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"character\"]},\"A recurring feature in a work of literature\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"motif\"]}}}', '[1,2]', 1),
(42, 'Vocab list 7', 'JeweledVessel39', '{\"desc\":\"Benas\",\"contnt\":{\"a place of safety; a harbor\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"haven\"]},\"a tract of barren wasteland\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"heath\"]},\" gray or white with age; impressively or venerably old\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"hoary\"]},\"a reverential regard; the relationship between a feudal lord and his master.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"homage\"]},\"one who receives or entertains guests; a large number or multitude; V = to receive or entertain socially\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"host\"]},\"a\\u00a0 person promoting human welfare and social reform\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"humanitarian\"]},\"a feigning to be what one is not or to believe what one does not\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"hypocrisy\"]},\"a bar or hindrance\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impediment\"]},\"to urge or drive forward or on as if by the exertion of strong moral pressure\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impel\"]},\"to bring into peril or danger\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"imperil\"]},\"marked by extreme calm and steadiness\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"imperturbable\"]},\"marked by impulsive passion or vehemence\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impetuous\"]},\" to strike or dash, esp. with a sharp collision; to encroach or infringe\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impinge\"]},\"inopportune; V = to request or urge for urgently\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"importune\"]},\"acting momentarily\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impulsive\"]},\"to lay the responsibility or blame for, often falsely or unjustly\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impute\"]},\"not endowed with life or spirit; not animated or lively\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"inanimate\"]},\"invested with bodily and human nature\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"incarnate\"]},\"severe as in weather or temper (archaic)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"inclement\"]},\"\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"incumbent\"]}}}', '[14,2]', 1),
(43, 'Vocab 7 (better)', 'JeweledVessel39', '{\"desc\":\"\",\"contnt\":{\"a place of safety; a harbor\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"haven\"]},\"a tract of barren wasteland\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"heath\"]},\" gray or white with age; impressively or venerably old\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"hoary\"]},\"a reverential regard; the relationship between a feudal lord and his master.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"homage\"]},\"one who receives or entertains guests; a large number or multitude; V = to receive or entertain socially\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"host\"]},\"a\\u00a0 person promoting human welfare and social reform\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"humanitarian\"]},\"a feigning to be what one is not or to believe what one does not\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"hypocrisy\"]},\"a bar or hindrance\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impediment\"]},\"to urge or drive forward or on as if by the exertion of strong moral pressure\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impel\"]},\"to bring into peril or danger\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"imperil\"]},\"marked by extreme calm and steadiness\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"imperturbable\"]},\"marked by impulsive passion or vehemence\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impetuous\"]},\" to strike or dash, esp. with a sharp collision; to encroach or infringe\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impinge\"]},\"inopportune; V = to request or urge for urgently\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"importune\"]},\"acting momentarily\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impulsive\"]},\"to lay the responsibility or blame for, often falsely or unjustly\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impute\"]},\"not endowed with life or spirit; not animated or lively\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"inanimate\"]},\"invested with bodily and human nature\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"incarnate\"]},\"severe as in weather or temper (archaic)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"inclement\"]},\"imminent (archaic); N = the holder of an office or ecclesiastical benefice\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"incumbent\"]}}}', '[2,14,1]', 1),
(44, 'English Vocabulary 11+12', 'JBR33ZY', '{\"desc\":\"\",\"contnt\":{\"ADJ = pleased; willing; inclined; compelled (all are archaic)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Fain\"]},\"N = fidelity of feudal tenant to his lord\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Fealty\"]},\"N = a deed notable esp. for courage\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Feat\"]},\"Adj = evil (archaic); having the quality of a (---)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Felonious\"]},\"ADJ = agitated; confused\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Flustered\"]},\"N = a fault due to weakness esp. of a moral character\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Frailty\"]},\"N = a trench in the earth made by a plow; a deep wrinkle 2. V = to make (---)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Furrow\"]},\"N = bile; bitter something bitter to endure; flaw (archaic) 2. V = to fret or wear away by friction\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Gall\"]},\"ADJ = clothed in vivid colors; tastelessly showy; flashy\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Garish\"]},\"N = an embellishment or decoration; V = to embellish or decorate\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Garnish\"]},\"ADJ = ostentatious or tasteless ornaments; garish\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Gaudy\"]},\"ADJ = relating to or characteristic to a whole group or class\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Generic\"]},\"ADJ = of or relating to marriage or generation (the ~ bed - John Milton); marked by diffusing sympathy or friendlinessGlean = V to gather bit by bit\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Genial\"]},\"N = a surface luster; V = to make appear right and acceptable\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Gloss\"]},\"V =to come to grips with; wrestle\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Grapple\"]},\"ADJ = tending to associate with others; social\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Gregarious\"]},\"V = to humble oneself or act in an abject manner as if in great fear or utter servility; to lie or crawl in a prostrate position as if in abject humility\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Grovel\"]},\"ADJ = regarded as holy, venerated, or sacred\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Hallowed\"]},\"N = a place of shelter or refuge; V = to give shelter or refuge\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Harbor\"]},\"V to gather bit by bit\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Glean\"]},\"Characterized with lack of influence of fate; a psychological or moral flaw in the main character; subplots; differing settings; spectacle (sometimes) onstage\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Shakespearean Tragedy\"]},\"Characteristics of this kind of person: exceptional\\/important; high rank; downfall makes a big impact on those around them; they cause their own downfalls through their actions\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Shakespearean Tragic Hero\"]},\"Dramatic convention where a character turns aside to speak to a few words directly to the audience\\/another character.\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Aside\"]},\"Dramatic convention where character makes big speech alone on stage; often honest\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Soliloquy\"]},\"A long speech in a play delivered by a single person; part of a conversation between one or two other people;\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Monologue\"]},\"Event\\/detail chronologically out of proper time in history\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Anachronism\"]},\"Prevailing mood\\/feeling of literary work\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Atmosphere\"]},\"Attitude a writer takes toward their subject, character, or audience\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Tone\"]},\"Personality\\/traits of a character (don&#039;t overthink this)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Character\"]},\"a distinctive feature or dominant idea in an artistic or literary composition that appears many times throughout the work\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Motif\"]}}}', '[9,1,2,14]', 1),
(45, 'Vocab 8', 'JeweledVessel39', '{\"desc\":\"Lists 15\\/16\",\"contnt\":{\"filled with anger aroused by something unjust\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"indignant\"]},\"incapable of error; not liable or mislead\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"infallible\"]},\"having a reputation of the worst kind\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"infamous\"]},\"a writ granted by a court whereby one is required to do or refrain from doing a specified act\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"injunction\"]},\"a slight indication, hint, or clue\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"inkling\"]},\"a quality of being insultingly contemptuous\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"insolence\"]},\"firm adherence to a code of moral or artistic values\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"integrity\"]},\"not marked by moderation\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"intemperate\"]},\"a space of time between periods or states\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"interval\"]},\"to petition for help or support\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"invoke\"]},\"intense and usually openly displayed anger\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"ire\"]},\"relating to, containing, or constituting contrast between the expected and reality\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"ironic\"]},\"marked by or suggestive of high spirits and lively mirthfulness\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"jocund\"]},\"discreet, showing good judgement\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"judicious\"]},\"range of vision\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"ken\"]},\"V = to ring, esp. for death or funeral; sound in an ominous manner; VT = to summon as if by knell; N = a stroke or sound of a bell; an indication of the end or failure\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"knell\"]},\"carrying a load or burden\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"laden\"]},\"the people of a religious faith as distinguished from its clergy\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"laity\"]},\"to express sorrow or mourning; N = a crying out in grief; elegy;  complaint\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"lament\"]},\"a harsh satire usually directed against an individual; a light, mocking satire; V = to make the subject of a lampoon; to ridicule\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"\"]}}}', '[8,2]', 1),
(47, 'English 13+14 Vocab', 'bitfeller', '{\"desc\":\"Vocab list for 13+14\",\"contnt\":{\"(N) a place of safety; a harbor\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"haven\"]},\"(N)\\u00a0a tract of barren wasteland\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"heath\"]},\"(adj) gray or white with age; impressively or venerably old\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"hoary\"]},\"(N)\\u00a0a reverential regard; the relationship between a feudal lord and his master\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"homage\"]},\"(N) one who receives or entertains guests; a large number or multitude\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"host\"]},\"(V)\\u00a0to receive or entertain socially\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"host\"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0promoting human welfare and social reform\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"humanitarian\"]},\"(N)\\u00a0a feigning to be what one is not or to believe what one does not\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"hypocrisy\"]},\"(N) a bar or hindrance\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impediment\"]},\"(V)\\u00a0to urge or drive forward or on as if by the exertion of strong moral pressure\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impel\"]},\"(V)\\u00a0to bring into peril or danger\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"imperil\"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0marked by extreme calm and steadiness\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Imperturbable \"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0marked by impulsive passion or vehemence\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"Impetuous \"]},\"(V)\\u00a0to strike or dash, esp. with a sharp collision; to encroach or infringe\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impinge\"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0inopportune\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"importune\"]},\"(V)\\u00a0to request or urge for urgently\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"importune\"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0acting momentarily\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impulsive\"]},\"(V)\\u00a0to lay the responsibility or blame for, often falsely or unjustly\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"impute\"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0not endowed with life or spirit; not animated or lively\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"inanimate\"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0invested with bodily and human nature\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"incarnate\"]},\"(adj) severe as in weather or temper (archaic)\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"inclement\"]},\"(adj)\\u00a0imminent (archaic)\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"incumbent\"]},\"(N)\\u00a0the holder of an office or ecclesiastical benefice\\r\":{\"type\":\"txt\",\"ans\":[\"incumbent\"]}}}', '[1,14,2]', 1);
